Iranian students are willing to die for their country's nuclear program.
They formed a human shield.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around nuclear installations in Iran.
With his gesture they wish to express their support for his country's nuclear programme in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
The students began to pray on Tuesday at noon in front of the facilities and then chanted death slogans to the United States and Israel.
Several hundred university students formed on Tuesday in the Iranian city of Isfahan human shields around the nuclear technology center where they work with uranium.
They intend to demonstrate their willingness to defend their country ' s nuclear programme with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), in a recent report, found that Iran, according to all indications, is struggling to obtain nuclear weapons.
In Israel, there is talk of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
The students began praying at noon at the nuclear facilities in Isfahan and then launched death slogans against the US and Israel.
