Daily menu of an obese child: don't eat breakfast and dinner sausages
More than one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity affects 5 per cent.
Obese children mostly come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
The importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference, is again demonstrated.
At the table, obsessed children eat, for example, sausages at least twice as often as children in families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had had French fries the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a chance".
In families of overweight children there is no practice of sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and took part in almost 900 basic education children from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program of "Obesity of Not a Chance", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th grade.
An adequate diet and plenty of exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obese children.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals per day according to the diet: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," reports one of the survey results.
No breakfast but with a snack for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, they are also important details, which also count, such as having a fixed hour for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone has breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that 10% of households have nothing to eat.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children, French fries are consumed much more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink sweet soft drinks daily (70%).
As a rule, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed sport, but among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make Your Diet
The next phase of the study allowed the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets based on all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy food, are far removed from the ideal."
Among its favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"The popularity of sweet soft drinks is above all alarming," the final report of the study warns.
As main food you take the palm paste and follow closely the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject the vegetable and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who completed the questionnaire after the end of the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", in many cases an important change was made in favor of the principles of healthy eating", is pointed out in the results of the study.
It draws attention, for example, to the issue of sweet drinks, where many children would start to prefer normal and running water.
Children would also more frequently choose in the questionnaire poultry meat and fish for the main meal and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour products.
