In Need for Speed: The Run competes all over America.
Review
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of improper carelessness of a routine trip during tomorrow's shift.
To some extent, the expectations were met, but this is of no use, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was meant to be done.
The new delivery, to which the title is added The Run, raised high expectations already before its premiere.
I promised that I would give new air to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as a result of what I showed, it appears as a game that should not end up being a genre of action again without more.
We are also curious to know how the scenes would remain inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary greatly from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total calculation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In fact, mistakes cannot be called mistakes, but rather the incomprehensible misdemeanour of programmers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant to see, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find yourself a sandstorm that reduces visibility.
Instead, in the mountains you have to be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a number of required rivals (normally in a classic race), then you try to buy time (chronographed classic duel) and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes the police appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are quite fewer landscapes in the game than could be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of the previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look somewhere else.
But a race conceived with a lot of action suits this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer true of collisions.
Of such games you can not expect it to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight advance or running the car with a normal traffic, there are only light rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
Resets are programmed in such a way that when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five resets are available for each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is only a help in case something goes wrong, but it is not very reliable.
Sometimes, even reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, it is necessary to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you gloat especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you have to turn or stop.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed because the "surprise" will always happen in front of your noses.
The adversaries also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always advance you to the same site.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can make the car tickle.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you right away.
And it's a shame, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if the merit is taken the idea with fifty exclusive clues or the classification in the race so that it doesn't fit boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during the races.
You have to pay attention to the gas suppliers next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, strong American cars for straight motorways and exotic supersports for technical driving, for example, on mountain roads with bends.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
When reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you reach the metro tunnel (pass), where you run dark down the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, from behind you arrive the convoy of the metro and you are taken forward without more.
In the writing we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one even thought a little or whether the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
It is a pity that, in the most tense moments, image quality is reduced and sometimes in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of their father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game only for their music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is thus quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble affirming that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
Fun is assured, but be prepared because mistakes will strike you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
The choirs of Carolina University will participate in the concert "Students of Tertipelo".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Third World Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Festa Academica.
During the event, twenty choirs from high school and university centres will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Václav Hampl", said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the high school choir concert, which will be held on March 17 at 2 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The programme is attended by Czech jazzist Karel Růžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Terciopelo" will be held in the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, where university choirs, including the Carolina Uninversity choir, will participate.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Day of Students with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Third World Revolution, but also to present coral music to the public at the highest level and promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the events were supported by the Mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the Rector of Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a series of musical events, improvised student shows and morning concerts.
More information can be found on the festival page www.festaaacademica.cz
