In his speech, the Minister-President said that he did not agree with the project's arguments that the federal executive could not structure through general rules the measures for the public administration to be prepared.
"I do not consider that if I did so, the autonomy of the regulatory body would be affected," he recalled that the planning of public policies in strategic areas such as the telecommunications sector is the responsibility of the federal executive, who has the constitutional mandate, the rectorate of the state.
The replacement of analog signals with digital signals is one of the most important changes the world has undergone in recent years, and results in better use of the radio spectrum, better signal quality and more channels.
